==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conveyor
<hw>Con*vey"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<def>A contrivance for carrying objects from place to place; esp., one
for conveying grain, coal, etc., -- as a spiral or screw turning in a
pipe or trough, an endless belt with buckets, or a truck running along a
rope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conviciate</ent>⟦br⟧
